cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. The paper proposes a novel approach that combines generative and discriminative models to learn compact and discriminative feature representations for visual tracking. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also uses the Laplacian coding algorithm, which is a machine learning technique, to learn the feature representations. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper also involves solving an optimization problem to jointly learn the feature representations and the correlation filter. This suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.RO (Robotics). 

Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed approach on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
